SrxTextIterator

public SrxTextIterator(SrxDocument document,
                       java.lang.String languageCode,

Creates text iterator that obtains language rules form given document using given language code. To retrieve language rules calls SrxDocument.getLanguageRuleList(String).

Parameters:
document - Document containing language rules.
languageCode - Language code to select the rules.
text - Text.

SrxTextIterator

public SrxTextIterator(SrxDocument document,
                       java.lang.String languageCode,
                       java.io.Reader reader,
                       int length,
                       int bufferSize)
Creates streaming text iterator that obtains language rules form given document using given language code. To retrieve language rules calls SrxDocument.getLanguageRuleList(String). To handle streams uses ReaderCharSequence, so not all possible regular expressions are accepted. See ReaderCharSequence for details.

Parameters:
document - Document containing language rules.
languageCode - Language code to select the rules.
reader - Reader from which text will be read.
length - Length of stream in reader.
bufferSize - Reader buffer size. Segments cannot be longer than this value.
